If. A primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc.

str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
From out, out from among, from, suggesting from the interior outwards. A primary preposition denoting origin, from, out.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.

str2: (a) I am powerful, have (the) power, (b) I am able, I can. Of uncertain affinity; to be able or possible.
From kata and luo; to loosen down, i.e. to demolish; specially to halt for the night.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.

str2: A prolonged form of a primary heuro, which heureo is used for it in all the tenses except the present and imperfect to find.
